CC  Members of this protein include MocA, which transfers cytosine from CTP to molybdopterin during molybdopterin cytosine dinucleotide (MCD) cofactor biosynthesis. It is distantly related to MobA, the  GTP:molybdopterin guanylyltransferase. The MocA family is particularly closely related in phylogenetic distribution to other markers of selenium-dependent molybdenum hydroxylases (SDMH), suggesting most SDMH must use MCD rather than molybdopterin guanine dinucleotide.
